  "example": {
    "code": "import flopscope as fnp\n\nf = fnp.array([1, 2, 4, 7, 11, 16])\n\nfnp.gradient(f)\n\nfnp.gradient(f, 2)\n\nx = fnp.arange(f.size)\n\nfnp.gradient(f, x)\n\nx = fnp.array([0., 1., 1.5, 3.5, 4., 6.])\n\nfnp.gradient(f, x)\n\nfnp.gradient(fnp.array([[1, 2, 6], [3, 4, 5]]))\n\ndx = 2.\n\ny = [1., 1.5, 3.5]\n\nfnp.gradient(fnp.array([[1, 2, 6], [3, 4, 5]]), dx, y)\n\nx = fnp.array([0, 1, 2, 3, 4])\n\nf = x**2\n\nfnp.gradient(f, edge_order=1)\n\nfnp.gradient(f, edge_order=2)\n\nfnp.gradient(fnp.array([[1, 2, 6], [3, 4, 5]]), axis=0)\n\nx = fnp.array([0., 2., 3., 6., 8.])\n\ny = x ** 2\n\nfnp.gradient(y, x, edge_order=2)\n\ndx = 2\n\nx = fnp.array([0., 2., 4., 6., 8.])\n\ny = x ** 2\n\nfnp.gradient(y, dx, edge_order=2)\n\ndx = 2\n\ndy = 3\n\nx = fnp.arange(0, 6, dx)\n\ny = fnp.arange(0, 9, dy)\n\nxs, ys = fnp.meshgrid(x, y)\n\nzs = xs + 2 * ys\n\nfnp.gradient(zs, dy, dx)  # Passing two scalars\n\nfnp.gradient(zs, y, dx)  # Passing one array and one scalar",
